_comment_READMEFIRST: *** Please turn off 'Automatic Formatting' and 'Format on Paste' for JSON files (Text Editor > JSON > Advanced) to avoid your IDE reformatting the file ***
_comment_READMESECOND: *** Don't forget to diff the file (with all whitespace diffs turned on) in Perforce before submitting ***
_comment_AdditionalFeatures: Additional configs to load at end
_comment_ValkyrieProjectSettings: General settings to apply to user-created projects
_comment_ValkyrieBlueprintGraph: Properties related to BP graphs, which may include data for Anim Graphs, Control Rig, etc.
_comment_ValkyrieAnimationSettings: Properties related to AnimBPs, ControlRig, Sequencer, etc. See also: ValkyrieBlueprintSettings
_comment_ValkyrieAudioSettings: Properties related to Audio including SoundWaves, SoundCues, Metasounds, etc.
_comment_ValkyrieUMGSettings: Properties related to UMG, including the UMG editor and MVVM framework
_comment_ValkyrieEditorUtilitySettings: Properties related to EditorUtility, affecting top level Utilities menu (TODO) & scripted actions. Widgets must also be added to LevelEditor tab allowlist.

ValkyrieEditorUtilitySettings._comment_AllowedEditorUtilityWidgets: Generates widget entries for the Level Editor Utility menu. Should be grouped by sub-categories for menu
ValkyrieEditorUtilitySettings._comment_AllowedEditorUtilityActions: Generates action entries for the Level Editor Utility menu. Should be grouped by sub-categories for menu

_comment_ValkyrieEditorSettings: Properties related to core editor functionality, restricting editor views/controls, allow lists for assets and classes, etc.

ValkyrieEditorSettings._comment_AllowedEditorModes: The FName defining each editor mode that appears in the toolbar of the level editor
ValkyrieEditorSettings._comment_AllowedContentBrowserFolders1: The list of folder names that can appear under the 'All' folder. Everything else will be hidden, except for user projects.
ValkyrieEditorSettings._comment_AllowedContentBrowserFolders2: Note that /Game is not here, and /Fortnite and /Epic are not real folders. These are aliases used to pick and choose which Fortnite assets are visible via FortExposedAssetLists.
ValkyrieEditorSettings._comment_AdditionalClassPickerDefaults: The default options that appear in the 'wizard' dialog when creating new assets for particular types
ValkyrieEditorSettings._comment_AllowedAssetTypes1: Rules for controlling ONLY Content Browser actions and Data Asset types. To allow classes for validation that aren't created in the Content Browser (or are BPs), use AllowedClasses.
ValkyrieEditorSettings._comment_AllowedAssetTypes2: Avoid exposing Import/Export controls for types that don't support them or only support T3D. Do not set Subclasses=True unless you're sure there are subclasses to expose.
ValkyrieEditorSettings._comment_AllowedAssetTypes3: Note: Which Data Assets are creatable must go in AllowedClasses, but in order to be viewable in the Content Browser they must also be marked Visible in AllowedAssetTypes
ValkyrieEditorSettings._comment_AllowedClasses1: List of all classes and structs exposed to UEFN, which means they are allowed to be referenced directly by user-created assets and actors.
ValkyrieEditorSettings._comment_AllowedClasses2: Classes marked with Visible: true will appear in class pickers such as for Blueprint parent classes, UClass* FProperties, etc.
ValkyrieEditorSettings._comment_AllowedClasses3: Note: All Blueprints must be listed in FortExposedAssetLists. BPs should only be listed here if they are subclassable (Visible:true), but must still go in a FortExposedAssetList.
